+# Hugo Repository - Agent Notes
+
+## Project Overview
+Hugo is a static site generator written in Go. The main codebase is in /workspace/hugo.
+
+## Key Packages
+- `metrics/` - Template performance metrics tracking (used by `--templateMetrics` and `--templateMetricsHints`)
+- `tpl/partials/` - Template partial execution; calls `TrackValue` for metrics hints
+- `common/types/` - Type utilities including `TypeToString` for template type conversions
+- `helpers/` - General utilities including `HashString` for hash-based comparisons
+
+## Known Issues and Fixes
+
+### --templateMetricsHints showing 0 for all templates (Issue #7048)
+**Root cause**: `diff.add()` in `metrics/metrics.go` had a wrong condition `!hreflect.IsTruthful(v)` for setting the baseline. Since most template values are "truthful" (non-nil, non-empty), the baseline was never set, and `howSimilar(v, nil)` always returned 0.
+
+**Fix**: Changed condition to `d.count == 0` to correctly initialize the baseline on first call.
+
+Also improved `howSimilar` to handle:
+- Type-checking via `reflect.TypeOf` (mismatched types return 0)
+- Fast path for comparable types via `==` operator
+- `template.HTML` and other HTML template types via `types.TypeToString`
+- Hash-based comparison as fallback for non-comparable types (maps, etc.)
+
+## Testing
+- Run `go test ./metrics/...` to test metrics package
+- The go vet tool (from a different go installation) may panic during test runs - this is unrelated to the codebase itself
+- Pre-existing failing test: `TestJSEscaping` in `tpl/internal/go_templates/texttemplate`
